==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin [[pulmonarius]] (of the lungs) < ''pulmonem'' (accusative of [[pulmo]], lung) < Proto-Indo-European '''*pleu-''' (to flow, to float, to swim). Cognate with Greek [[πλεμόνι]], Lithuanian [[plauciai]] (lungs), Russian [[плавать]] (to swim).

===Adjective===
'''pulmonary'''

# Pertaining to, having, or affecting the [[lung]]s. 

====Synonyms====
* [[pneumonic]]
* [[pulmonic]]
 
====Derived terms====
*[[pulmonary embolism]]
*[[pulmonary tuberculosis]]

